 *
 * This implementation follows secure‑by‑design principles:
 *   • No use of scanf/gets – avoids format‑string and buffer‑overflow risks.
 *   • Fixed‑size buffer with explicit bounds checking.
 *   • Proper handling of EOF and I/O errors.
 *   • New‑line character is consumed but not stored.
 *   • Returns the exact number of characters placed in the buffer.
